  "content": "y);\n  }\n\n  .tier-row {\n    display: flex; align-items: stretch; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;\n  }\n  .tier-card {\n    flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<!-- SLIDE 1: COVER -->\n<div class=\"slide\" style=\"background: linear-gradient(160deg, #0f172a 0%, #1a1a3e 50%, #0f172a 100%);\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">A Developer's Discovery</div>\n  <div class=\"cover-center\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 72px; margin-bottom: 32px;\">&#128200;</div>\n    <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"font-size: 58px; line-height: 1.12;\">\n      My AI Agent Can<br>\n      Finally See Inside<br>\n      <span class=\"highlight\">the System It Builds.</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 22px;\">\n      OpenTelemetry traces + an MCP control plane<br>\n      for the AI agent building my Rust product.\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"cover-tags\">\n      <span class=\"tag\">OpenTelemetry</span>\n      <span class=\"tag\">MCP</span>\n      <span class=\"tag\">Rust</span>\n      <span class=\"tag\">AI Agents</span>\n      <span class=\"tag\">Control Plane</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">01 / 08</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- SLIDE 2: THE PROBLEM -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">The Problem</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    The Agent Builds It.<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-red\">But Can't See It.</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 32px;\">\n    I'm building an organizational memory system in Rust. An AI agent<br>\n    (Claude Code) writes the code, runs the tests, ships the commits.<br>\n    But when something is slow or broken, it's flying blind.\n  </div>",
